<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,158,436]" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,255,158,184]" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Note:</emphasis>
—In the phylogenetic tree (
<figureCitation box="[571,638,158,184]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,187,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[151,1436,187,1840]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogram generated from Maximum Likelihood (RAxML) analyses, based on ITS-β-tubulin-α-actin matrix. ML bootstrap supports (≥ 75%) and Bayesian posterior probability (≥ 0.95) are indicated as ML/BYPP. The tree is rooted to Amphilogia gyrosa (YMJ 91123101). Type strains are in bold and newly generated strains are in red bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796575" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796575/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Long &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[665,821,158,184]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis box="[665,821,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clustered together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Q. R. Li &amp; J. C. Kang. However" authorityName="Q. R. Li &amp; J. C. Kang. However" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tetrastigmae">
<emphasis box="[1099,1272,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. tetrastigmae</emphasis>
Q.R. Li &amp; J.C. Kang. However
</taxonomicName>
, the ascospores of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Long &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[529,684,194,220]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis box="[529,684,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[976,1148,195,220]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tetrastigmae">
<emphasis box="[976,1148,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. tetrastigmae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(42.0–62.0 × 6.7–12.0 µm vs. 72.5–111.5 × 12.5–19.5 µm), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Long &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[564,809,230,256]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis box="[564,809,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Rosellinia verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(GMB0082) ascospores are completely surrounded by a thin slimy sheath, but the 
<taxonomicName box="[433,605,267,292]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tetrastigmae">
<emphasis box="[433,605,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. tetrastigmae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only has the slime at the ends (
<bibRefCitation author="Xie, X. &amp; Liu, L. &amp; Zhang, X. &amp; Long, Q. &amp; Shen, X. &amp; Boonmee, S. &amp; Kang, J. C. &amp; Li, Q. R." box="[968,1146,266,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" pagination="183 - 196" refId="ref10966" refString="Xie, X., Liu, L., Zhang, X., Long, Q., Shen, X., Boonmee, S., Kang, J. C. &amp; Li, Q. R. (2019) Contributions to species of Xylariales in china - 2. Rosellinia pervariabilis and R. tetrastigmae spp. nov. and a new record of R. caudata. Mycotaxon 134: 183 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 134.183" type="journal article" year="2019">
Xie 
<emphasis box="[1019,1070,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, stromata of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Long &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[536,708,303,328]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tetrastigmae">
<emphasis box="[536,708,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. tetrastigmae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(630–735 µm high × 525–700 µm diam. vs. 
<quantity box="[1221,1370,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="400.0" valueMax="500.0" valueMin="300.0">300–500 mm</quantity>
high × 
<quantity box="[136,284,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="500.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="400.0">400–600 mm</quantity>
diam.). And 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Long &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[427,580,338,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis box="[427,580,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[706,842,339,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="emergens">
<emphasis box="[706,842,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. emergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Petrini, L. E." box="[927,1068,338,364]" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" refId="ref9079" refString="Petrini, L. E. (2013) Rosellinia: a world monograph. Bibliotheca Mycologica, J. Cramer: Stuttgart, 410 pp." type="book" year="2013">Petrini 2013</bibRefCitation>
) but it is different from the species which have whole spore length germ silt in this group for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Long &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[800,955,374,400]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Rosellinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis box="[800,955,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">R. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ascospores are completely surrounded by a thin slimy sheath.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
